TYPE ERROR: Default body of 'speak' in interface 'Sp' launders an effect: the body performs <Stdout>, which is not sourced from any argument and is not declared by the method's effect row, so a caller can instantiate the method's effect variable to <> and a value typed pure would silently perform it. Declare the effect as a concrete label in the method's row, or perform it only through an argument so the caller sees it.